entries.title: Benedict’s Burial Leaves Francis Alone, and Unbound
entries.description: Liberal supporters of Francis, a pope never shy about exercising power, now anticipate a late-breaking season of change.

entries.title: African Journalists Urge Senegal to Release Pape Alé Niang
entries.description: Pape Alé Niang, an investigative reporter, was arrested on charges of disclosing confidential government information. Journalists and rights defenders say he was just doing his job.

entries.title: Mali Pardons Detained Ivorian Soldiers
entries.description: Ivory Coast had said the 49 soldiers were in Mali to provide security for a United Nations peacekeeping mission, but Mali had accused them of being mercenaries.

entries.title: Ukrainians Celebrate Orthodox Christmas at a Holy Site Long Linked to Moscow
entries.description: The mass marked a deeply symbolic moment as the head of the church that is loyal to Kyiv delivered a sermon after months of tension with the Moscow-led branch.

entries.title: Wells Fargo Executive Fired After Air India Urination Allegation
entries.description: The executive, for the Indian subsidiary of Wells Fargo, was fired after the investigation became public. Air India faces scrutiny for how it handled the matter.

entries.title: Broken Promises
entries.description: If you’ve already broken your New Year’s resolution, don’t despair. You don’t need a holiday to change your life.

entries.title: High Food Prices Rile Up Canadians
entries.description: Grocery stores have become a lightning rod for consumer discontent amid inflation and lingering mistrust after a bread price-fixing scandal.

entries.title: As Asian Societies Age, ‘Retirement’ Just Means More Work
entries.description: Across East Asia, populations are graying faster than anywhere else in the world, and while younger generations shrink, older workers are often toiling well into their 70s and beyond.

entries.title: In a Ukraine Workshop, the Quest to Build the Perfect Grenade
entries.description: A Ukrainian unit is tinkering with tape, a scale, a 3-D printer and other items to turn a fragmentation grenade into a tank-killer. It’s a steep and risky challenge.

entries.title: Ant Group Says Its Founder, Jack Ma, Will Relinquish Control
entries.description: Ant Group, the fintech sister company of the e-commerce behemoth Alibaba, is one of China’s most influential companies.
